    <div class="content-dark">
      <h1 class="text-center">DOs and DON'Ts</h1>

      <div class="dos-donts">
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> hug and shake hands with people.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> ensure proper disinfection before making any physical contact if you must.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> spend the entire day without washing hands.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> wash your hands frequently with soap and water or, use an alcohol-based hand rub. This will remove the virus if it is on your hands.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> spend time close to a person who has fever and is coughing or sneezing.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> maintain reasonable distance between yourself and someone who is coughing, sneezing (at least 1 meter/3.5 feet apart).</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> cough or sneeze without any cover in an open environment.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> cover your mouth and nose with tissue or a handkerchief when coughing and sneezing. Throw away the used tissue immediately and wash your hands with soap and water or use an alcohol-based hand rub. If neither tissue nor handkerchief is within reach, use your armpit or elbow region to block your cough or sneeze and clean up afterwards.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> go to public places, offices and public gatherings despite having flu-like symptoms (fever, cough, sneeze etc).</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> remain at home to avoid infecting others.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> frequently touch your eyes, nose and mouth without cleaning them using soap and water or hand sanitizer.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> avoid touching your eyes, nose and mouth. Hands touch many surfaces which can be contaminated with the virus and you can transfer the virus from the surface to yourself.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> roam around and go into public exposure without a mask despite having flu-like symptoms.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> use face masks to cover the nose and mouth and stay home in a well-ventilated room if you have flu-like symptoms.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> self-medicate with antibiotics based on assumptions about symptoms.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> seek medical care immediately if you have fever, cough and difficulty in breathing. If possible, call a health worker and alert them about your condition.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> spit in public, on roads, sidewalks etc.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> spit into a basin, sink, toilet, drain or some other inlet into the sewage system.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> use frequently used surfaces and objects as we do during normal times, without cleaning them regularly.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> clean and disinfect frequently touched surfaces such as doorknobs/handles, car doors, elevator buttons etc. daily with regular household disinfectant or soap and water.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row advice">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="dont">
              <h5><strong>DON'T</strong> ignore all guidelines or home quarantine instructions given by health officials after traveling to some place from a corona affected region.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="do">
              <h5><strong>DO</strong> follow guidance given by health workers at the airport and other border entry points when traveling from a corona affected country or region.</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

